Women's Health Initiative in the US and the Million Women Study in the UK are the two largest studies into the effects of hormone replacement therapy . 
  Both found strong evidence HRT increases a woman's risk of breast, womb and ovarian cancers . 
  The combined oestrogen and progesterone HRT therapy doubled the risk of cancer up to eight years after stopping treatment . 
  Women who use combined HRT for more than 10 years have double the risk . 
 